  <num>28:2A-204</num>
  <heading>Formation in general.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>A lease contract may be made in any manner sufficient to show agreement, including conduct by both parties which recognizes the existence of a lease contract.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>An agreement sufficient to constitute a lease contract may be found although the moment of its making is undetermined.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(c)</num>
    <text>Although one or more terms are left open, a lease contract does not fail for indefiniteness if the parties have intended to make a lease contract and there is a reasonably certain basis for giving an appropriate remedy.</text>
  </para>
